    "attempts": 2,
    "on_failure": true
  },
  "notifications": {
    "recipients": ["anna", "ops"]
  }
}
```

A few things to confirm before pasting into CI:

- `timezone` — swap `"UTC"` for your actual timezone (e.g. `"America/New_York"`)
- `recipients` — replace `"anna"` and `"ops"` with the actual email addresses or channel names your CI system expects
- `skip_holidays` — most schedulers don't support this natively; you may need a wrapper script or a plugin to handle it, depending on your CI platform (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, etc.)

Which CI system are you using? I can tailor the format to match it exactly.
